<title type="html"><![CDATA[Mixing with waveform generators]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5801&amp;p=53549#p53549"><![CDATA[
You could do 4-bit DAC playback with the square channels, but that would need precise timing to write the new samples regularly, and you already have a nicer 7-bit channel to do the same with.  The NES isn't really powerful enough to do software samples and run a game at the same time.<br /><br />Of course, you could always fake it and use DMC samples that sound like square/triangle sound effects.  Zelda 1's sword is a recording of the FDS sound effect played through the DMC channel.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Sat Dec 05, 2009 3:58 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
